    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9294" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑφαίνω, ὑφάω</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑφόωσιν</span>, ipf. iter. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑφαίνεσκον</span>, aor. 1 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὕφηνα</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">weave</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἱστόν</span>, ‘at the
          loom.’ (The Greek loom stood upright, like the Roman loom represented
          in the cut, or like the Egyptian loom in cut No. 59.) Fig.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">devise, contrive</span>, as we say ‘spin,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δόλον, μῆτιν, ι 422</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.678</span></i>. 
